1.2 计算 Q 值¶

Q-Learning Q-Learning Value IterationPolicy Iteration-ValueUtility

Q-Learning Q - Q

$$ q(s_{t},a) = R_{t+1} + \gamma \times\max_a q(a,s_{t+1}) $$

- $(s_{t},a)$ $a$ $R_{t+1}$ $a$ $s_{t+1}$Q $\max_a q(a,s_{t+1})$$\gamma$

Q $alpha$ Q

$$ q(s_{t},a) = (1-\alpha) \times q(s_{t},a) + \alpha \times(R_{t+1} + \gamma \times\max_a q(a,s_{t+1})) $$

2 $q(s_{t},a)$

$s_1$ u $s_2$ Q u: -24r: -13d: -0.29l: +40$\gamma$ 0.9

$$ \begin{align} q(s_{t},a) & = R_{t+1} + \gamma \times\max_a q(a,s_{t+1}) \\ & =(-0.1) + (0.9)*(40) \\ & =(35.9) \end{align} $$

1.3 如何选择动作¶

-

  1. Q Q

epsilon-greedy Q

3 epsilon-greedy

In [1]:
import random

actions = ['u','r','d','l']
qline = {'u':1.2, 'r':-2.1, 'd':-24.5, 'l':27}
epsilon = 0.3 # 0.3

def choose_action(epsilon):
    action = None
    if random.random() < epsilon: # 
        action = random.choice(actions)
    else: 
        action = max(qline)
    return action

epochs = [20,50,80]
epsilon0s = [0.1, 0.3, 0.5, 0.7, 0.9]
alphas = [0.1, 0.3, 0.5, 0.7, 0.9]
gammas = [0.1, 0.3, 0.5, 0.7, 0.9]
def plot_parameters(epoch=50, epsilon0=0.5, alpha=0.5, gamma=0.9):
    print("prameters values: epoch=%d, epsilon0=%.1f, alpha=%.1f, gamma=%.1f" % (epoch, epsilon0, alpha, gamma))
    r = Robot(g,alpha=alpha, epsilon0=epsilon0, gamma=gamma)
    r.set_status(learning=True)
    runner = Runner(r, g)
    runner.run_training(epoch, display_direction=True)
    runner.plot_results()

print("______________epoch effects______________")
for epoch in epochs:
    plot_parameters(epoch=epoch)
    
print("______________epsilon effects______________")
for epsilon0 in epsilon0s:
    plot_parameters(epsilon0=epsilon0)
    
print("______________alpha effects______________")
for alpha in alphas:
    plot_parameters(alpha=alpha)
    
print("______________gamma effects______________")
for gamma in gammas:
    plot_parameters(gamma=gamma)
